Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.
Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and
mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Mince @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{};
season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread carrots
out across entire sheet.)

Roast on top rack for ~{12%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

While carrots roast, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup
water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil; cover
and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep
covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; sear,
turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Once carrots have roasted 12 minutes, carefully add seared chicken to empty side
of sheet; wipe out pan. (For 4 servings, leave carrots roasting and add chicken
to a second #baking sheet{}; roast on middle rack.) Return to top rack until
carrots are browned and tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}
more.

Remove from oven; let chicken rest on sheet for ~{5%minutes}. Sprinkle carrots
with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.

> Swap in pork or salmon for chicken. Cook until pork is cooked through, 3-5
> minutes per side, or cook salmon (skin sides down) until skin is crisp,
> 5-7 minutes, then flip and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more.
> (Skip roasting!) Transfer to a cutting board to rest; cook through remaining
> step as instructed.

== Hot Honey Sauce ==

Heat half the @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings) and @butter{½%TBSP} in
same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and half the ginger (add more
if desired). Cook until fragrant and softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @hot honey{½%ounce}, and ¼ cup water (1/3
cup for 4). Bring to a simmer; cook until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove
from heat.

Stir in @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4); season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Cilantro Lime Rice ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in cilantro, lime zest, juice from half the lime,
and @butter{½%TBSP} (1 TBSP for 4). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in scallion greens and any resting juices from chicken to pan with sauce.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Slice salmon crosswise when serving (skip slicing for salmon!).

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Divide chicken, rice, and carrots between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and
serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.